results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #142
results.description: In the present, the X-Men fight against the Brotherhood of Mutants. In the future, they battle the deadly mutant-killing Sentinels. And linking these two worlds, these two desperate battles, is Katherine Pryde. The fate of mutantkind is in her hands!

textObjects.text: In the present, the X-Men fight against the Brotherhood of Mutants. In the future, they battle the deadly mutant-killing Sentinels. And linking these two worlds, these two desperate battles, is Katherine Pryde. The fate of mutantkind is in her hands!

The text on the front cover says it all: "This issue: Everbody dies!" With Chris Claremont and John Byrne's team-up coming to an end, they went all out to conclude "Days of Future Past," the ultimate time-travel, everything's gone wrong tales.
